div.p:
MINE hoſt was one of thoſe geniuſes, who, like MACKLIN's Sir Pertinax Mac Sycophant, depended more upon bowing than on education and natural abilities,
he could never ſtand ſtraight in the preſence of a gueſt;
and to the pliability of Sir Pertinax, he added the complaiſance of SHAKESPEARE's Polonius, being ever of the ſame opinion with the perſon he converſed with, unleſs that perſon was his wife, or one of his ſervants; and theſe he eternally contradicted, whether they were right, or whether they were wrong.—
